Arlette Ricci was ‘particularly determined’ to stash money in Swiss accounts for more than two decades . 
  She is the owner of the Nina Ricci fashion company and is one of Europe’s richest women . 
  She denied hiding the equivalent of more than £15million and was given a total of three years in prison . 
  Her daughter Margot Vignat was also convicted and given a suspended sentence . 
  Judge said she was 'particularly determined' to hide money in HSBC accounts . 
 